cmceer16300101204a571h5ws	The CSO guide to top security conferences	There is nothing like attending a face-to-face event for career networking and knowledge gathering, and we don’t have to tell you how helpful it can be to get a hands-on demo of a new tool or to have your questions answered by experts. Fortunately, plenty of great conferences are coming up in the months ahead. If keeping abreast of security trends and evolving threats is critical to your job — and we know it is — then attending some top-notch security conferences is on your must-do list for 2025.\nFrom major events to those that are more narrowly focused, this list from the editors of CSO, will help you find the security conferences that matter the most to you. We’ll keep it updated with new conferences so check back often. While we don’t expect this calendar to be comprehensive, we do aim to have it be highly relevant. If there’s something we’ve missed, let us know. You can email your additions, corrections and updates to Samira Sarraf>.\nJuly 2025\nCydes 2025, Putrajaya, Malaysia: 1-3 July\nCyberX, Jakarta, Indonesia: 2 July\nAISA SydneySec, New South Wales, Australia: 3 July\n#RISK New York, New York, US: 9-10 July\nFutureCon Orange County Cybersecurity Conference, California, US: 10 July\nBSides Bangalore, Karnataka, India: 11 July\nPittsburgh Cybersecurity Conference, Pennsylvania, US: 11 July\nBSides Brisbane, Queensland, Australia: 12 July\nBSides Mumbai, Maharashtra, India: 12 July\nCSA Non-Human Identity Summit, virtual: 15-16 July\nSANS 2025 Government Security Forum, virtual: 22 July\nCISO Melbourne, Victoria, Australia: 22-23 July\nGovernance 360 Africa: Cyber | Fraud | Resilience, Mombasa, Kenya: 22-24 July\nCISO-CIO Forum, California, US: 23 July\nGartner Security & Risk Management Summit, Tokyo, Japan: 23-25 July\nFutureCon Denver Cybersecurity Conference, Colorado, US: 24 July\nDigital Forensics & Incident Response (DFIR) Summit & Training, virtual and Utah, US: 24-31 July\nDenver Cybersecurity Conference, Virtual and Colorado, US: 25 July\nBSidesABQ, New Mexico, US: 25-26 July\nDFIR Summit & Training 2025, Virtual and Utah, US: 24-31 July\nAugust 2025\nBlack Hat USA, Nevada, US: 2-7 August\nAcceleRISE, Massachusetts, US: 4-6 August\nIEEE Cyber Security and Resilience, Crete, Greece: 4-6 August\nCISO Chicago, Illinois, US: 6-7 August\nDEF CON 32, Nevada, US: 7-10 August\nSANS Security Awareness Summit & Training 2024, Virtual and Illinois, US: 11-15 August\nDigital Trust Hui Taumata, Wellington, New Zealand: 13 August\n34th USENIX Security Symposium, Washington State, US: 13-15 August\nFutureCon Omaha, Nebraska, US: 14 August\nChicago Cybersecurity Conference, Illinois, US: 21 August\nFutureCon Salt Lake City, Utah, US: 21 August\nBxsec, TBC São Paulo, Brazil: 23 August\nASIAL Security Conference, Sydney, Australia: 27-29 August\nSecureWorld Critical Infrastructure, virtual: 28 August\nLinux Security Summit, Amsterdam, Netherlands: 28-29 August\nSeptember 2025\nINFOSEK, Nova Gorica, Slovenia: 3-5 September\nFutureCon Charlotte Cybersecurity Conference, North Carilina, US: 4 September\nCyberhagen, virtual and Copenhagen, Denmark: 4 September\nBlue Team Con 2024, Chicago, Illinois: 4-7 September\nGartner IT Symposium/Xpo, Queensland, Australia: 8-11 September\n16th Annual Billington Cybersecurity Summit, Washington, DC, US: 9-12 September\nIdentity Week, Washington, DC, US: 10-11 September\nNordic Cyber Summit, Scandinavia, Copenhagen: 10-11 September\nFutureCon Milwaukee Cybersecurity Conference, Wisconsin, US: 11 September\nFinancial Services Summit, London, England: 11 September\nCrowdStrike Fal.Con, Nevada, US: 15-18 September\nFranSec, Paris, France: 16-17 September\nNational Insider Threat Symposium, Washington, DC, US: 17-18 September\nAotearoa AI Summit, Auckland, New Zealand: 18 September\nHealthcare Security Summit, New York, US: 18 September\nGartner Security & Risk Management Summit, London, UK: 22-24 September\nGoogle Cloud Summit Switzerland, virtual: 24 September\n#RISK AI, London, UK: 25 September\nFutureCon Des Moines Cybersecurity Conference, Iowa, US: 25 September\nGlobal Security Exchange (GSX), Louisiana, US: 29 September – 1 October\n#CS4CA, London, UK: 30 September\nInternational Cyber Expo, London, UK: 30 September – 1 October\nOctober 2025\nHacker Halted, Georgia, US: 1-2 October\nSecureWorld Dallas, Texas, US: 2 October\nRelativity Fest, Illinois, US: 7-9 October\nSecureWorld Denver, Colorado, US: 9 October\nRedHat Summit Connect, London, UK: 9 October\nManuSec, Illinois, US: 14-15 October\nNIST Cybersecurity Career Week Summit, Virtual: 17 October\nSecureWorld Atlanta, Georgia, US: 23 October\nInfoSec World, Florida, US: 27-29 October\n#CS4CA, São Paulo, Brazil: 28-29 October\nSecureWorld New York City, NY, US: 29 October\nNovember 2025\nBenelux Cyber Summit, Amsterdam, Netherlands: 4-5 November\nFraud Prevention Summit, New York, US: 5 November\nUKSec, London, UK: 11-12 November\nFebruary 2026\n#CS4CA ANZ, Perth, Australia: 10-11 February\nApril 2026\nCyphercon, Wisconsin, US: 1-2 April	https://www.csoonline.com/article/559539/the-cso-guide-to-top-security-conferences.html	2025-06-27 06:00:00	https://www.csoonline.com/article/559539/the-cso-guide-to-top-security-conferences.html	\N	\N	CRITICAL	cmcdybhtx000rpav7h2p7uahg	f	2025-06-27 06:05:00.459	<div id="remove_no_follow">\n\t\t<div class="grid grid--cols-10@md grid--cols-8@lg article-column">\n\t\t\t\t\t  <div class="col-12 col-10@md col-6@lg col-start-3@lg">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class="article-column__content">\n<section class="wp-block-bigbite-multi-title"><div class="container"></div></section>\n\n\n\n<p>There is nothing like <a href="https://www.csoonline.com/article/539824/data-protection-security-conferences-why-go.html">attending a face-to-face event</a> for career networking and knowledge gathering, and we don’t have to tell you how helpful it can be to get a hands-on demo of a new tool or to have your questions answered by experts. Fortunately, plenty of great <a href="https://www.computerworld.com/article/1622033/2022-new-zealand-tech-conference-and-event-guide.html">conferences</a> are coming up in the months ahead. If keeping abreast of security trends and evolving threats is critical to your job — and we know it is — then attending some top-notch security conferences is on your must-do list for 2025.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>From major events to those that are more narrowly focused, this list from the editors of CSO, will help you find the security conferences that matter the most to you. We’ll keep it updated with new conferences so check back often. While we don’t expect this calendar to be comprehensive, we do aim to have it be highly relevant. If there’s something we’ve missed, let us know. You can email your additions, corrections and updates to <a href="mailto:samira_sarraf@foundryco.com" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Samira Sarraf</a>>.</span></p>\n\n\n\n<h3 class="wp-block-heading" id="july-2025">July 2025</h3>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://cydes.my/">Cydes 2025</a>, Putrajaya, Malaysia: 1-3 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://indonesia.cyberxglobal.com/">CyberX</a>, Jakarta, Indonesia: 2 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://aisasecuritydays.com.au/sydneysec">AISA SydneySec</a>, New South Wales, Australia: 3 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://www.risknewyork.com/">#RISK New York</a>, New York, US: 9-10 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://futureconevents.com/events/orange-county-ca-2025/">FutureCon Orange County Cybersecurity Conference</a>, California, US: 10 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://events.bsidesbangalore.in/event/acsc2025#register">BSides Bangalore</a>, Karnataka, India: 11 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://futureconevents.com/events/pittsburgh-pa-2024" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Pittsburgh Cybersecurity Conference</a>, Pennsylvania, US: 11 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://bsidesbrisbane.com/">BSides Brisbane</a>, Queensland, Australia: 12 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://www.bsidesmumbai.in/">BSides Mumbai</a>, Maharashtra, India: 12 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://web.cvent.com/event/d6ce07a4-af1e-4e53-a4a7-6a04059214cb/websitePage:5b909f5e-65f8-43b1-97dd-19ea9a7435f8?RefId=Event%20Website">CSA Non-Human Identity Summit</a>, virtual: 15-16 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://www.sans.org/webcasts/2025-sans-government-security-forum/">SANS 2025 Government Security Forum</a>, virtual: 22 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://ciso-mel.coriniumintelligence.com/">CISO Melbourne</a>, Victoria, Australia: 22-23 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://www.pulseconferences.com/conference/governance-360-africa-congress/">Governance 360 Africa: Cyber | Fraud | Resilience</a>, Mombasa, Kenya: 22-24 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://planetcybersec.com/072325-conference/">CISO-CIO Forum</a>, California, US: 23 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://www.gartner.com/jp/conferences/apac/security-risk-management-japan" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Gartner Security &amp; Risk Management Summit</a>, Tokyo, Japan: 23-25 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://futureconevents.com/events/denver-co-2025/">FutureCon Denver Cybersecurity Conference</a>, Colorado, US: 24 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://www.sans.org/cyber-security-training-events/digital-forensics-summit-2025/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Digital Forensics &amp; Incident Response (DFIR) Summit &amp; Training</a>, virtual and Utah, US: 24-31 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://futureconevents.com/events/denver-co-2024" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">Denver Cybersecurity Conference</a>, Virtual and Colorado, US: 25 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://bsides.org/w/page/12194156/FrontPage">BSidesABQ</a>, New Mexico, US: 25-26 July</p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href="https://www.sans.org/cyber-security-training-events/digital-forensics-summit-2025/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener">DFIR Summit &amp; Training 2025</a>, Virtual and Uta