cmcf218i4002s1204dv522xzy	Food Retail Giant's Breach: 2.2 Million Employees Affected	Personal Data Stolen in Ransomware Hit, Says Dutch Owner of Stop & Shop, Giant Food\nFood retail giant Ahold Delhaize USA is notifying 2.2 million current and former employees, as well as an unspecified number of employees in the Netherlands, that a November 2024 data breach exposed their personally identifiable information, including Social Security numbers and medical details.	https://www.databreachtoday.com/food-retail-giants-breach-22-million-employees-affected-a-28842	2025-06-27 16:56:47.69	https://www.databreachtoday.com/food-retail-giants-breach-22-million-employees-affected-a-28842	\N	https://130e178e8f8ba617604b-8aedd782b7d22cfe0d1146da69a52436.ssl.cf1.rackcdn.com/food-retail-giants-breach-22-million-employees-affected-image_file-4-a-28842.jpg	HIGH	cmcf217cf002o1204950aiju7	f	2025-06-27 16:56:47.692	<img src="https://130e178e8f8ba617604b-8aedd782b7d22cfe0d1146da69a52436.ssl.cf1.rackcdn.com/food-retail-giants-breach-22-million-employees-affected-image_file-4-a-28842.jpg" align=right hspace=4><b>Personal Data Stolen in Ransomware Hit, Says Dutch Owner of Stop & Shop, Giant Food</b><br>Food retail giant Ahold Delhaize USA is notifying 2.2 million current and former employees, as well as an unspecified number of employees in the Netherlands, that a November 2024 data breach exposed their personally identifiable information, including Social Security numbers and medical details.	{ransomware,healthcare,retail,usa,severity-high,incident-data-breach,year-2025}	\N	{}	A data breach has been reported. Severity level: high. Stolen in Ransomware Hit, Says Dutch Owner of Stop & Shop, Giant Food\nFood retail giant Ahold Delhaize USA is notifying 2	1. Consider engaging external cybersecurity experts\n2. Activate incident response team immediately\n3. Review access controls and user permissions\n4. Implement data encryption at rest and in transit\n5. Conduct security awareness training	2025